<TITLE> Balloon-seller dies after gas tank explodes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 14 (bdnews24.com)A balloon-seller died Monday, after one of his gas tanks exploded in Dhanmondi amid New Year celebrations. Sub inspector Rezaul Karim of Dhanmondi police told bdnews24.com the young man, named Babu, died around 1.30pm after being rushed to Dhaka's Orthopaedic Hospital at Sher-e-Bangla Nagar with critical injuries. Eleven year-old Manik, a witness to the incident, said: "There was a loud noise at Dhanmondi lakeside just before 1.00pm." "Then we saw a man who fell in the water trying to make his way back to the shore." "When he came close, we saw he had lost both his legs," said Manik, adding that the man was then rushed to hospital. Sub inspector Karim said Babu was using two gas tanks to fill his balloons, when one of the tanks suddenly exploded.
